    • toJsonArrayIfNotAllZeros

      public static <T> java.util.Optional<com.google.gson.JsonArray> toJsonArrayIfNotAllZeros​(java.util.List<T> list)
      If the items in the supplied list are all numbers (double, BigDecimal, or even PreciseValue / ImpreciseValue), returns empty optional. Otherwise, returns the items as a JsonArray. If the items are numbers, these get converted to jsonDouble with 6 digits of accuracy.
